place.name: CHILTON CANTELO
place.gazetteerText: CHILTON-CANTILO, a parish in Yeovil district, Somerset; on the river Yeo, near the East Somerset railway, 3¼ miles N of Yeovil. Post town, Yeovil. Acres, 631. Real property, £1, 774. Pop., 112. Houses, 24. The property is divided among a few. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Bath and Wells. Value, £260.* Patron, H. Goodford, Esq. The church is very good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
